==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Blowgun
<hw>Blow"gun`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A tube, as of cane
or reed, sometimes twelve feet long, through which an arrow (sometimes
poisoned) or other projectile may be impelled by the force of the
breath. It is a weapon much used by certain Indians of America and the
West Indies; -- called also <altname>blowpipe</altname>, and
<altname>blowtube</altname>. See <er>Sumpitan</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>blowhard</ent>⟦br⟧
